{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, other neural network architectures, such as sequence-to-sequence models using transformer neural networks 72, or graph-to-graph-based architectures utilizing diffusion-based models 20, could be implemented.",
    "These variations would enable additional ligand-based design approaches.",
    "The graphto-graph models would extend the capability to incorporate 3D information for structure-based molecular design, while sequence-tosequence models would be limited to protein sequence information.",
    "Furthermore, the drug-target interactome could be expanded to include additional targets beyond those considered in the presented study.",
    "For example, RNA binding sites, protein surface binders such as molecular glues or certain macrocycles, or protein-protein interactions could be included."
  ]
}